DUTSE – It has been observed that the shortage of manpower, modern operational tools, and lack of periodical training in modern security operations, and guidelines for security personnel are some of the challenges responsible for the lingering insecurity in the country. Dr. Yahuza Getso, a retired security personnel, stated this in an interview with Daily Independent in Dutse as he proffers the way forward. “It was quite unfortunate that we are lacking enough manpower, modern operational tools, and the laziness of personnel to attend professional training, and courses for improved skills and expertise. How then can we confront the daunting security challenges,” he asked. According to Dr. Gets, the manpower in the army is grossly inadequate, talk less of the police force that is a little above thirty thousand personnel nationwide. “With outdated operational tools, how then can we boast of confronting our enemies who are well trained and equipped with modern security gadgets of warfare.